---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Dance — Movement Terms That Score Big"
  description="Dance terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. WALTZ (17pts), JIVE (14pts), POLKA (11pts), TWERK (12pts). Dance vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble dance words, waltz scrabble points, jive scrabble, polka scrabble word, dance terms scrabble, movement words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Dance — Movement Terms That Score Big","description":"Dance terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. WALTZ (17pts), JIVE (14pts), POLKA (11pts), TWERK (12pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-dance"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is WALTZ a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! WALTZ scores 17 points (W=4, A=1, L=1, T=1, Z=10). It's a ballroom dance in triple time. The Z tile alone contributes 10 of the 17 points, making it one of the best short Z words available."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is JIVE worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"JIVE scores 14 points (J=8, I=1, V=4, E=1). It's a lively swing dance from the 1940s. With J (8pts) and V (4pts), it clears two of the trickiest mid-to-high value tiles in just 4 letters."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is POLKA valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. POLKA scores 11 points (P=3, O=1, L=1, K=5, A=1) and is a fast Central European dance. The K tile provides nearly half the score. POLKAS (12pts) with an S is also valid."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Dance — Movement Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Dance names are Scrabble power words. WALTZ delivers the Z tile beautifully, JIVE dumps J and V together, and POLKA clears the K. These aren't obscure terms — everyone knows them, which makes them easy to recall mid-game. Short, punchy, and loaded with high-value tiles.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">WALTZ (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JIVE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">POLKA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWERK</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Dance Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">WALTZ — 17 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">W=4, A=1, L=1, T=1, Z=10 · 5 letters · Z+W combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The elegant ballroom dance in triple time. WALTZ is a Z-word masterpiece — 17 points from just 5 tiles (3.4 per tile). It uses the Z with W, clearing two awkward consonants in one play. Plus it hooks to WALTZED (19pts) and WALTZES (18pts).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💃 JIVE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · J=8, I=1, V=4, E=1 · Swing dance</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🕺 TWERK</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · T=1, W=4, E=1, R=1, K=5 · Hip-hop dance</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎵 POLKA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · P=3, O=1, L=1, K=5, A=1 · Czech dance</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🩰 RUMBA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · R=1, U=1, M=3, B=3, A=1 · Latin dance</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Dance Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SAMBA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TANGO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SALSA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MAMBO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOXTROT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">17pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FANDANGO</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Dance Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WALTZ is the best 5-letter Z word:</span> At 3.4 points per tile, WALTZ outscores longer Z words for efficiency. W=4 and Z=10 do all the work while A, L, T are common fillers you'll almost always have available.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">JIVE clears J+V together:</span> J (8pts) and V (4pts) are both awkward tiles. JIVE uses both in one 4-letter word for 14 points. That's two problem tiles solved simultaneously with minimal rack commitment.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Dance words hook well:</span> WALTZ→WALTZED, JIVE→JIVED/JIVES, POLKA→POLKAS, TANGO→TANGOS. Most dance names take standard English suffixes, giving you extension options on future turns.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Dance words solve the <span class="text-white font-medium">Z, J, V, K, and W problem tiles</span> — all five of the trickiest mid-to-high value consonants. WALTZ (Z+W), JIVE (J+V), POLKA (K), and TWERK (W+K) give you a dance for every difficult rack combination.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid dance word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-chess/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Chess</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-camping/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Camping</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-textiles/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Textiles</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-pottery/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Pottery</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-philosophy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Philosophy</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
